.SH DESCRIPTION
These routines read the attributes of
.I XilKernel
kernel objects.  Kernels are used in image convolution, error diffusion, painting,
and band combine operations.  The key values specify the key pixel 
position - a position relative to the upper left corner of the kernel.  
The key pixel aligns with the output pixel and constrains which input 
pixels are used to generate the output.
.P
.IX xil_kernel_get_height
.IX Functions xil_kernel_get_height
.IX "Kernel Functions" "xil_kernel_get_height"
.BR xil_kernel_get_height (\^)
gets the height of a kernel.
.P
